Temrs_Para_25: Security and access to the OpenMarkets Equix App
Temrs_Para_26: You are solely responsible for your own anti-virus and mobile device security measures and those of any authorised user. You are responsible to ensure that no unauthorised persons have access to your OpenMarkets trading account and that you must keep your security information such as usernames, passwords and access codes secure. You acknowledge and agree that you are responsible for transactions on your OpenMarkets trading account using the OpenMarkets Equix App including where you fail to keep access to the OpenMarkets Equix App secure and OpenMarkets will consider trades placed on your OpenMarkets trading account via the OpenMarkets Equix App to be authorised by you. If you have enabled fingerprint or facial recognition access on your OpenMarkets Equix App, you should not have any fingerprints or facial recognition records stored on your device other than your own. If other people use their fingerprints or facial recognition on your device, you should turn off fingerprint and facial recognition access for the OpenMarkets Equix App.
Temrs_Para_27: If you, or someone else, change the fingerprint or facial recognition settings on your device, as a security measure fingerprint and/or facial recognition access will be disabled for the OpenMarkets Equix App and you will be prompted to enter your PIN or password to log on to the OpenMarkets Equix App. Only re-enable fingerprint or facial recognition access if you are sure the changes made to your fingerprint or facial recognition settings on your device were made by you.  OpenMarkets is not responsible for any malfunction in fingerprint or facial recognition functionality or changes to fingerprint or facial recognition technology that impacts the way you access the OpenMarkets Equix App.
Temrs_Para_29: The OpenMarkets Equix App may allow you to elect to receive alerts via a push notification service or email. Alerts sent via push notification will be sent to any device on which you have installed and registered the OpenMarkets Equix App with notifications enabled. Alerts could be seen by others (including unauthorised persons) who use or access your device. It is your responsibility to check the "Notifications" settings on all your devices to ensure the privacy and alerts settings are appropriate for your use.
Temrs_Para_30: Changes to OpenMarkets Equix App Terms and Conditions of Use
Temrs_Para_31: Any amendment to the OpenMarkets Equix App Terms and Conditions of Use will be published in the OpenMarkets Equix App and can be accessed on the OpenMarkets Equix App menu. You agree your continued use of the OpenMarkets Equix App after receiving notice of an amendment to the OpenMarkets Equix App Terms and Conditions of Use will constitute your agreement to the amended OpenMarkets Equix App Terms and Conditions of Use.

content_1: You can set up and customise your own favourite screen layout and save them for later usage.
content_2: The first thing you can do to protect your account is to set your PIN. The OpenMarkets Equix Web will be auto-locked after 5 minutes of inactivity. If anything looks suspicious, you can change your PIN immediately, other sessions will be immediately forced log-out.
content_3: Related news tab shows ASX announcements that are related to stocks in personal watch-list and portfolio. All market tab displays everything that is submitted to ASX.
